 of Thailand]], as well as a member of the [[WOSM-Asia-Pacific Region|Asia Pacific Regional Scout Committee]]. Yongyudh was the Charter President of the [[Rotary Club]] of Bangkok-Banglamphu District 3350, [[Rotary International]], in 1998. Yongyudh is a chairman of Interdisciplinary network of the Royal Institute of Thailand.\n\n==Awards==\n* 1978 -Fellow of the Royal Institute of Thailand\n* 1987 - [[File:The Boy Scout Citation Medal 1st class (Thailand) ribbon.png|80px]] Boy Scout Citation Medal of Vajira (First Class)<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|title=Corporate Profile|url=http://biothai.tripod.com/W1.html|work=Bangkok Biomaterial Center website|publisher=Bangkok Biomaterial Center|accessdate=2010-08-22|year=2000}}</ref>\n* 1989 - [[File:Palmes academiques Officier ribbon.svg|80px]] Officier dans l\u2019[[Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]] (France)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1989 - [[File:Order of the Crown of Thailand - 1st Class (Thailand) ribbon.svg|80px]] Knight Grand Cross (First Class) of the Most Noble [[Order of the Crown of Thailand]]<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1991 - [[File:Fr Nat Order of Merit ribbon.jpg|80px]] Chevalier de l\u2019[[Ordre national du M\u00e9rite]] (France)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1991 - [[File:Order of the White Elephant - 1st Class (Thailand) ribbon.svg|80px]] Knight and Dame Grand Cross (First Class) of the Most Exalted [[Order of the White Elephant]]<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1992 - [[File:Order of Ramkeerati (Thailand) ribbon.png|80px]] Member of the [[Order of Ramkeerati|Order of Symbolic Propitiousness Ramkeerati]] Boy Scout Citation Medal (Special Class)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1995 - [[File:Freeman Safeguarding Medal - Class 2 Cat 2 (Thailand).png|80px]] Freemen Safeguarding Medal (Second Class, Second Category)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1996 - [[File:Order of the Crown of Thailand - Special Class (Thailand) ribbon.svg|80px]] Knight Grand Cordon (Special Class) of the Most Noble [[Order of the Crown of Thailand]]<ref name=\"CTB\">{{cite journal|last=von Versen|first=R\u00fcdiger|author2=Glyn O. Phillips |title=Honorary Membership of EATB 1999 \u2013 Professor Dr. Med. Yongyudh Vajaradul (2nd World Congress and 8th EATB Annual Meeting, October 7\u201310, 1999, Warsaw, Poland)|journal=Cell and Tissue Banking|date=2000-03-01|volume=1|issue=1|pages=95|doi=10.1023/A:1017214023864|publisher=Springer Netherlands|issn=1389-9333}}</ref>\n* 1999 - [[File:National Order of Merit Officer Ribbon.png|80px]] Vajaradul was appointed an Officier d l'[[Ordre national du M\u00e9rite]] by Ambassador Coster, [[Diplomatic missions of France|Embassy of France to Thailand]] on 24 June 1999.<ref>{{cite web|title=Contribution of Prof. Dr. Med. Yongyudh Vajaradul to the enhancement of standards of Thai Medical Personnel|url=http://www.tatb.org/tatb_classic/w30.html|work=Thai Association of Tissue Banking website|publisher=Thai Association of Tissue Banking|accessdate=2010-08-22|year=2003}}</ref>\n* 1999 - Boy Scout Citation Medal of Vajira (Third Class)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1999 - Order of the Silver Elephant (First Class) - (All India Boy Scouts)<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n* 1999 - Yongyudh was awarded an honorary membership of the [[European Association of Tissue Banks]] (EATB) at the Second World Congress and Eighth EATB Annual Meeting, October 7\u201310, 1999, in [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]].<ref name=\"CTB\"/>\n* 1999-Order of the Silver Tiger (first Class) Bangladesh\n* 2008 - He was awarded the [[Bronze Wolf Award]] by the [[World Scout Committee]] during the 38th [[World Scout Conference]] held in 2008 on Jeju Island, Korea.<ref>{{cite web |title=38th World Scout Conference \u2013 Summary |url=https://www.scout.org/node/6817 |work=World Scout Bureau website |publisher=World Scout Bureau |accessdate=26 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20050220074238/http://161.246.11.90/tatb/ls-8.htm\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20080311022537/http://sunsite.nus.edu.sg/nuhtb/apastb.htm\n*http://www.ingentaco